modules.description: Handles event channel operations such as binding, unbinding, and notifying remote domains. Works with event channel descriptors and interrupt vectors to manage asynchronous communication. Used to coordinate data transfer between unikernels and Xen hypervisor, enabling efficient event-driven I/O.

Converts event channels to and from integers, initializes and closes event channel interfaces, and manages notifications and bindings. Handles interdomain communication by linking local channels to remote domains or ports, and binds channels to specific virtual interrupts. Used to establish and control event-based communication between domains in a virtualized environment.

Tracks and manages a sequence of values using a mutable generation counter. It wraps values in a tagged structure, allows conditional extraction, and supports resuming operations based on generation state. Used to safely track and restore state in concurrent or iterative processes.
